WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:02.260 --> 00:00:07.590
If the HP Touchsmart screen does not work
after upgrading to Windows 8,

00:00:07.590 --> 00:00:11.330
installing an older touchscreen driver from
the Windows Update Catalog 

00:00:11.440 --> 00:00:12.880
can correct the problem.

00:00:13.670 --> 00:00:19.730
This video shows how to install an older touchscreen
driver from the Windows Update Catalog.

00:00:23.320 --> 00:00:27.220
From the computer desktop, open Internet Explorer.

00:00:27.980 --> 00:00:34.820
Type catalog.update.microsoft.com into the
browser's address bar,

00:00:34.829 --> 00:00:37.129
and then press Enter on your keyboard.

00:00:38.479 --> 00:00:42.879
If prompted, install the Microsoft Update
Catalog add-on.

00:00:44.190 --> 00:00:49.699
Type NextWindow in the search field, and then
press Enter on your keyboard.

00:00:49.699 --> 00:00:52.819
From the list of search results, find the driver named

00:00:52.819 --> 00:01:02.899
NextWindow - Input - NextWindow Voltron Touch Screen, version 3.1.6.0.

00:01:04.440 --> 00:01:07.200
Click Add next to the name of the driver.

00:01:08.160 --> 00:01:09.800
Click View Basket.

00:01:10.680 --> 00:01:11.760
Click Download.

00:01:12.900 --> 00:01:13.940
Click Browse.

00:01:14.660 --> 00:01:18.060
 If a user account control message
opens click Yes,

00:01:19.620 --> 00:01:22.600
and then choose where to save the downloaded file.

00:01:23.860 --> 00:01:25.860
The download may take a few minutes.

00:01:26.150 --> 00:01:29.090
When the download is complete, click Close.

00:01:32.040 --> 00:01:34.320
Open the downloaded folder named

00:01:34.320 --> 00:01:39.520
NextWindow - Input - NextWindow Voltron Touch
Screen.

00:01:40.620 --> 00:01:43.940
Double-click the .cab file to open it.

00:01:44.780 --> 00:01:46.380
Click the first file,

00:01:46.390 --> 00:01:51.980
and then press CTRL + A on your keyboard to
select all the files.

00:01:51.980 --> 00:01:56.020
Right-click on any selected file and select Copy.

00:01:57.300 --> 00:02:02.520
Click the Back arrow in the upper left corner
of the window to go back to the folder named

00:02:02.520 --> 00:02:07.700
NextWindow - Input - NextWindow Voltron Touch Screen.

00:02:08.979 --> 00:02:13.799
Right-click inside the blank or white portion
of the window and select Paste.

00:02:14.420 --> 00:02:19.300
All of the files from the .cab file are extracted
into this folder.

00:02:20.500 --> 00:02:33.540
Double-click the file named NWVoltronSetupLiteDesktop_3.1.6.0.f.exe.

00:02:33.999 --> 00:02:37.899
If a User Account Control message opens, click Yes.

00:02:38.820 --> 00:02:41.540
The driver Setup Wizard opens.

00:02:41.549 --> 00:02:44.359
Click Next to start the installation.

00:02:44.359 --> 00:02:47.799
Read and respond to the windows to install the driver.

00:02:52.620 --> 00:02:56.260
After the driver is installed, restart the computer.

00:02:57.180 --> 00:02:59.580
If the touch screen still does not work,

00:02:59.590 --> 00:03:04.590
please refer to another video showing how
to disable a graphics card.

00:03:08.020 --> 00:03:14.360
You can find additional helpful videos at
hp.com/supportvideos

00:03:15.000 --> 00:03:16.820
and on our YouTube channel,

00:03:17.080 --> 00:03:21.740
youtube.com/howto4U.

